-- Grasim, Shree Cement Gain After Nomura Holdings Raises Rating to `Neutral'
-- B y   S t e p h e n   F o x w e l l
-- 2010-10-06T03:34:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-06/grasim-shree-cement-gain-after-nomura-holdings-raises-rating-to-neutral-.html
Shree Cement Ltd. and Grasim
Industries Ltd. rose in Mumbai after Nomura Holdings Inc. raised
the stocks to “neutral” from “reduce.”  Shree Cement advanced 1.1 percent to 2,093.6 rupees and
Grasim gained 1.1 percent to 2,329.8 rupees  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
